<collectingCountry id="7D807647FFEAFFD51B0A454FFDE2FB6D" box="[516,567,1145,1171]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="C753F835FFEAFFD51B48454EFD52FB6D" box="[582,647,1144,1171]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Lima</collectingRegion>
). This species is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="DA2C8875FFEAFFD51D3E454FFBB5FB6D" box="[1072,1120,1145,1171]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Laraos District at ca. 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD519C145AAFEF3FB49" box="[207,294,1180,1207]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="m" value="5000.0">5000 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="9DAC2A52FFEAFFD5183645AAFEAAFB48" box="[312,383,1180,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1076,1098]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,196,1043]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[164,1423,187,1053]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution maps of Senecio phlomidifolius (red cross) and S. fernandinus (open circle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413882/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). It grows in rocky places on consolidated soils, usually under the protection of rocks. Some species that were observed in the same habitat are 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51BE045F6FBD5FB24" box="[750,1024,1216,1242]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dielsiochloa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floribunda">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51BE045F6FBD5FB24" box="[750,1024,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Dielsiochloa floribunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D1A45F6FBA3FB24" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1044,1142,1216,1242]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D8045F6FA79FB24" box="[1166,1452,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Englerocharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D8045F6FA79FB24" box="[1166,1452,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Englerocharis peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD5199E45D2FEF2FB01" authorityName="G.T.Burnett" authorityYear="1835" box="[144,295,1252,1279]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD5183245D2FDDDFB00" box="[316,520,1252,1278]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Nototriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tovarii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD5183245D2FDDDFB00" box="[316,520,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Nototriche tovarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51B1745D2FD4DFB01" box="[537,664,1252,1279]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51BA045D2FC54FB00" box="[686,897,1252,1278]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51BA045D2FC54FB00" box="[686,897,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Senecio canescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51A9F45D2FBA7FB00" box="[913,1138,1252,1278]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carhuanishoensis">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51A9F45D2FBA7FB00" box="[913,1138,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. carhuanishoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D8D45D2FB38FB00" box="[1155,1261,1252,1278]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nutans">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D8D45D2FB38FB00" box="[1155,1261,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. nutans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51DF345D2FA53FB00" box="[1277,1414,1252,1278]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51DF345D2FA53FB00" box="[1277,1414,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51C9845D2FF2DFADC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51C9845D2FF2DFADC" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. violifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD5183B443EFD97FADC" box="[309,578,1288,1314]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliolatum">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD5183B443EFD97FADC" box="[309,578,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Xenophyllum ciliolatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(all Compositae).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="052836D7FFEAFFD519B3441AFD00FAB9" blockId="1.[136,1452,532,2071]" box="[189,725,1324,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519B3441AFE96FAB8" bold="true" box="[189,323,1324,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Collected in flower in early June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4D8D655CFFEAFFD519B34466FEB3FA71" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="052836D7FFEAFFD519B34466FEB3FA71" blockId="1.[136,1452,532,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519B34466FE9DFA94" bold="true" box="[189,328,1360,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD518FF4466FD46FA94" authorityName="H. Beltran" authorityYear="2021" box="[497,659,1360,1386]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlomidifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD518FF4466FD46FA94" box="[497,659,1360,1386]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">phlomidifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the resemblance of the leaves to those of some species of 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD519864442FEB7FA71" authority="(Labiatae)" baseAuthorityName="Labiatae" box="[136,354,1396,1423]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Phlomis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519864442FF31FA70" box="[136,228,1396,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Phlomis</emphasis>
(Labiatae)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4D8D655CFFEAFFD619B344AEFEA3FF23" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="052836D7FFEAFFD519B344AEFBA4F89D" blockId="1.[136,1452,532,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519B344AEFE90FA4C" bold="true" box="[189,325,1432,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Discussion:</emphasis>
—Due to the habit, indumentum 
<typeStatus id="DA2C8875FFEAFFD51BA544AFFD0BFA4D" box="[683,734,1433,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
, and capitulum morphology, 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D1544AEFB02FA4C" authorityName="H. Beltran" authorityYear="2021" box="[1051,1239,1432,1458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlomidifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D1544AEFB02FA4C" box="[1051,1239,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. phlomidifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD519E3448AFD7DFA28" authority="Cuatrecasas (1960: 187)" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityPageNumber="187" authorityYear="1960" box="[237,680,1468,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519E3448AFE50FA28" box="[237,389,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="61064B26FFEAFFD5189E448AFD7DFA28" author="Cuatrecasas, J." box="[400,680,1468,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" pagination="182 - 195" refId="ref3686" refString="Cuatrecasas, J. (1960) Studies on Andean Compositae-IV. Brittonia 12 (3): 182 - 195. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2805052" type="journal article" year="1960">Cuatrecasas (1960: 187)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51BE8448AFB62FA28" authority="Montesinos &amp; R. Zarate" authorityName="Montesinos &amp; R. Zarate" box="[742,1207,1468,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51BE8448AFC49FA28" box="[742,924,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
Montesinos &amp; R.Zárate
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="61064B26FFEAFFD51DEC448AFEDBFA04" author="Montesinos, D. B. &amp; Pino, G. &amp; Zarate, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="199" pagination="213 - 223" refId="ref3793" refString="Montesinos, D. B., Pino, G. &amp; Zarate, R. (2018) Three new species of Senecio (Compositae: Senecioneae) from the Alto Maranon, Huanuco region, Central Peru. Phytotaxa 347 (3): 213 - 223. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 347.3.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Montesinos 
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51C61448BFA79FA28" box="[1391,1452,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">et al.</emphasis>
(2018: 219)
</bibRefCitation>
. From 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD5185344D6FE24FA04" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[349,497,1504,1530]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD5185344D6FE24FA04" box="[349,497,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known from 
<collectingRegion id="C753F835FFEAFFD51B8144D6FCDFFA04" box="[655,778,1504,1530]" country="Peru" name="Cajamarca" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Cajamarca</collectingRegion>
, the new species differs in shape and length of the basal leaf lamina (elliptic to oblong-elliptic, 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51B0A4732FDA7F9E1" box="[516,626,1540,1567]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12 cm</quantity>
vs. broadly lanceolate, 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51A764732FC0AF9E1" box="[888,991,1540,1567]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="6.25" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.5">5.5–7 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D0F4732FB46F9E0" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[1025,1171,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D0F4732FB46F9E0" box="[1025,1171,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), peduncle length (shortpedunculate, up to 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51857471EFE5BF9BD" box="[345,398,1576,1603]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
vs. long-pedunculate, 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51B87471EFD3AF9BD" box="[649,751,1576,1603]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="5.75" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="2.0">2–9.5 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51A1E471EFC76F9BC" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[784,931,1576,1602]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51A1E471EFC76F9BC" box="[784,931,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of supplementary bracts (18 to 22 vs. 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51986477AFF2BF998" box="[136,254,1612,1639]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="3.556" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="in" value="16.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="14.0">14 to 18 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD5180A477AFE42F998" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[260,407,1612,1638]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD5180A477AFE42F998" box="[260,407,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of florets (150 to 160 vs.&gt; 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51A3B477AFCAEF998" box="[821,891,1612,1638]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="in" value="200.0">200 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51A8E477AFBC6F998" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[896,1043,1612,1638]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51A8E477AFBC6F998" box="[896,1043,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), floret length (
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51DCF477AFA94F999" box="[1217,1345,1612,1639]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.55" metricValueMax="10.1" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="9.55" valueMax="10.1" valueMin="9.0">9–10.1 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51C62477AFF61F975" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="6.75" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.0">6–7.5 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD519D64746FEB9F974" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[216,364,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519D64746FEB9F974" box="[216,364,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and achene indumentum (glabrous vs. densely thick-pilose in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D354746FB1AF974" authorityName="Cuatrecasas" authorityYear="1960" box="[1083,1231,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellenbergii">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D354746FB1AF974" box="[1083,1231,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. ellenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Their distribution areas do not overlap. Regarding 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD518FB47A2FD72F950" box="[501,679,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD518FB47A2FD72F950" box="[501,679,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species can be distinguished by the leaf indumentum (laxly lanate on both surfaces vs. glabrous to densely arachnoid above, densely lanate beneath in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D81478EFA97F92C" box="[1167,1346,1720,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D81478EFA97F92C" box="[1167,1346,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), cauline leaf size (8–10 × 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD5185D47EAFE00F909" box="[339,469,1756,1783]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.7">0.7–2.5 cm</quantity>
, progressively decreasing in size upward vs. 1–6.5 × 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51D3047EAFB15F909" box="[1086,1216,1756,1783]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="cm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1.5 cm</quantity>
, abruptly decreasing in size upward in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD518544636FDDAF8E4" box="[346,527,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD518544636FDDAF8E4" box="[346,527,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of florets (150 to 160 vs. 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51AB84636FB86F8E4" box="[950,1107,1792,1819]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.3019999999999996" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="in" value="125.0" valueMax="130.0" valueMin="120.0">120 to 130 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D524636FAC4F8E4" box="[1116,1297,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D524636FAC4F8E4" box="[1116,1297,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and corolla length and color (
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD5185B4612FE0FF8C1" box="[341,474,1828,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.55" metricValueMax="10.1" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="9.55" valueMax="10.1" valueMin="9.0">9–10.1 mm</quantity>
, dark-yellowish vs. 
<quantity id="C26F9B32FFEAFFD51BCD4612FCF0F8C1" box="[707,805,1828,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 mm</quantity>
, pink-reddish when mature in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51D884612FAEEF8C0" box="[1158,1339,1828,1854]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51D884612FAEEF8C0" box="[1158,1339,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51C5A4612FECBF89C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseoandinus">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51C5A4612FECBF89C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Senecio roseoandinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="DA2C8875FFEAFFD51B3F467FFDB4F89D" box="[561,609,1865,1891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
locality in northwestern 
<collectingRegion id="C753F835FFEAFFD51A77467EFC0BF89C" box="[889,990,1864,1890]" country="Peru" name="Huanuco" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Huánuco</collectingRegion>
Department.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="052836D7FFEAFFD519B3465AFC8BF7E9" blockId="1.[136,1452,532,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD519B3465AFE68F878" authorityName="H. Beltran" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,445,1900,1926]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlomidifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD519B3465AFE68F878" box="[189,445,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Senecio phlomidifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also might be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51A0B465AFB99F878" authority="Cabrera (1966: 12)" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityPageNumber="12" authorityYear="1966" box="[773,1100,1900,1926]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keshua">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51A0B465AFCBAF878" box="[773,879,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. keshua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="61064B26FFEAFFD51A78465AFB99F878" author="Cabrera, A. L." box="[886,1100,1900,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref3419" refString="Cabrera, A. L. (1966) El genero Senecio en la Republica Argentina. I. La seccion Brachypappus. Revista del Museo de La Plata. Seccion Botanica 10 (44): 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1966">Cabrera (1966: 12)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species with pseudopetiolate basal leaves, lanate indumentum, and few nodding capitula. They can be differentiated by the indumentum 
<typeStatus id="DA2C8875FFEAFFD51C2446A7FA88F855" box="[1322,1373,1937,1963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
, which is densely lanate in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD518694682FE04F830" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1966" box="[359,465,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keshua">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD518694682FE04F830" box="[359,465,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. keshua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but laxly lanate in 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51BA54682FCBCF830" authorityName="H. Beltran" authorityYear="2021" box="[683,873,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlomidifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51BA54682FCBCF830" box="[683,873,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. phlomidifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Their distributions areas do not overlap; 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51C4F4682FA79F830" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1966" box="[1345,1452,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keshua">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51C4F4682FA79F830" box="[1345,1452,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. keshua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from northern 
<collectingCountry id="7D807647FFEAFFD5189546EEFE0DF80C" box="[411,472,2008,2034]" name="Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Chile</collectingCountry>
and northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="7D807647FFEAFFD51BA646EEFCC2F80C" box="[680,791,2008,2034]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="61064B26FFEAFFD51A2946EEFBDBF80C" author="Salomon, L. &amp; Sklenar, P. &amp; Freire S. E." box="[807,1038,2008,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref4074" refString="Salomon, L., Sklenar, P. &amp; Freire S. E. (2018) Synopsis of Senecio series Culcitium (Asteraceae: Senecioneae, Senecioninae) in the Andean region of South America. Phytotaxa 340 (1): 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 340.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Salomón 
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51A9A46EFFC18F80C" box="[916,973,2008,2034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) and its presence in 
<collectingCountry id="7D807647FFEAFFD51DF946EEFA9CF80C" box="[1271,1353,2008,2034]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
is likely (
<bibRefCitation id="61064B26FFEAFFD5199E46CAFEAEF7E8" author="Beck, S. G. &amp; Ibanez, D." box="[144,379,2044,2070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" pagination="361 - 367" refId="ref3097" refString="Beck, S. G. &amp; Ibanez, D. (2014) Senecio L. In: Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (Eds.) Catalogo de las Plantas Vasculares de Bolivia. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 127: 361 - 367." type="journal article" year="2014">Beck &amp; Ibáñez 2014</bibRefCitation>
, sub the heterotypic synonym 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFEAFFD51BDE46CAFC9BF7E8" box="[720,846,2044,2070]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zoellneri">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFEAFFD51BDE46CAFC9BF7E8" box="[720,846,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="199">S. zoellneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="052836D7FFE9FFD619B341A8FEA3FF23" blockId="2.[136,1451,158,221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">
Finding further populations of 
<taxonomicName id="C2974D54FFE9FFD61B1541A9FD0FFF46" authorityName="H. Beltran" authorityYear="2021" box="[539,730,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlomidifolius">
<emphasis id="37E3EAC5FFE9FFD61B1541A9FD0FFF46" box="[539,730,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">S. phlomidifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is essential in order to improve the knowledge of its variability and distribution area.
</paragraph>
